headline: Analysts See U.S. Airline Stock Turnaround. JetBlue, American Report This Week.
summary: Alaska Airlines got a bullish outlook from UBS, on the hopes it would continue a stock market turnaround from the back half of last year. JetBlue, American, and Southwest also report this week.

headline: What travelers can expect as Southwest Airlines introduces assigned seats
summary: Starting Tuesday, customers on Southwest flights will have assigned seats and the option of paying more to get their preferred seat closer to the front of a plane or seats with extra legroom.  Under the open-seat system, Southwest customers could check in starting exactly 24 hours before departure to secure places in boarding lines at departure gates.  Others landed in “B” or “C,” the likelihood of only middle seats being available rising the longer they waited to check in.
